-- Germany’s Neureuther, Slovenia’s Maze Win as Ski World Cup Ends
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-03-17T14:53:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-17/germany-s-neureuther-slovenia-s-maze-win-as-ski-world-cup-ends.html
Felix Neureuther of Germany won the
final men’s slalom as skiing’s World Cup season ended today,
beating Austria’s Marcel Hirscher into second spot.  Ivica Kostelic of Croatia came third at Lenzerheide,
Switzerland. World slalom champion Hirscher had already clinched
the overall and slalom World Cup titles.  Tina Maze  of Slovenia, who was already assured of the
women’s overall crown, won today’s giant slalom ahead of Tessa
Worley of France and Switzerland’s Lara Gut. Maze also won the
giant-slalom category for the season.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 